<title>CANADA: CANADA MAY WEEKLY EARNINGS RISE 3.0 PCT ON YEAR.</title>
<headline>CANADA MAY WEEKLY EARNINGS RISE 3.0 PCT ON YEAR.</headline>
<dateline>OTTAWA 1997-07-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>The preliminary estimate of average weekly earnings for Canadian workers in all industries except agriculture and fishing rose 3.0 percent in May from a year earlier to a seasonally adjusted C$604.56, Statistics Canada said on Friday.</p>
<p>From the month before, earnings rose 0.8 percent.</p>
<p>Seasonally adjusted payroll employment rose 0.1 percent in May to 11.23 million from an upwardly revised 11.22 million in April.</p>
